Clinic &amp; community hall torched in Joe Slovo Park CAPE TOWN - A clinic and community hall in Joe Slovo Park have been torched.It's thought that the overnight violence could be linked to protests over evictions in the area.City law enforcement officials are maintaining a strong presence in the area this morning.The City of Cape Town's JP Smith has condemned the violence. The behaviour is beyond defence as many residents use these facilities. There are residents who need chronic medication from the clinic and it will take a significant amount of time to repair the hall. Meanwhile, a MyCiTi bus was also set alight in the area on Sunday.MyCiti bus on fire in Joe Slovo Park pic.twitter.com/vN2NCKDQAI(Edited by Shimoney Regter)